s-functionally with key stakeholders to determine appropriate marketing KPIs across multi-channel marketing campaigns and programmes. Creating and managing tools and dashboards in CRM, analytics and marketing platforms to create insight and recommendations for continuous monitoring and optimization. Collaborating on analysis and interpretation of data with marketing, sales and other functions to drive marketing and business insights and data-driven decisions. Coaching, training and supporting marketing teams on marketing analytics, reporting, dashboards. Aligning marketing performance goals with budgets and planning. Managing ad-hoc marketing operations projects. Identifying areas for continuous improvement for marketing operations. Assumes responsibility for maintaining effective working relations, communication, and coordination with management and company personnel Setting goals in accordance with team objectives and tracks progress toward goals. Providing assistance to area personnel as needed. Keeping management informed of area activities and significant problems. Completing required reports and records accurately and promptly. Attending meetings as required. Assumes responsibility for related duties as required or assigned by Staying informed of developments in marketing performance analytics. Completing special projects as assigned. Any reasonable and lawful instruction related to work and given by an authorised person. PERSON SPECIFICATION Education/Certification Degree or post graduate qualification in Marketing, Business, Communications or equivalent. Experience Required Extensive experience in B2B technology within a digital marketing, marketing operations/analytics function. Previous experience of using CRM tools for creating reports and dashboards and analyzing data. Experience of analytics & BI tools, (e.g. Google Analytics, Google Data Studio, Google Tag Manager, Adobe Analytics, HotJar, advanced Excel, Tableau, Power BI), certifications an advantage. Marketing automation experience is advantageous. Proven ability to manage and deliver global marketing analytics in a fast-paced environment. Team Lead Experience. Knowledge Knowledge of digital marketing technologies, strategies, channels and appropriate analytics tools and metrics. Data visualization skills. Advanced MS Suite (PPT and Excel). Skills, abilities and attributes A natural problem solver with an ability to analyse data, provide insights and recommendations for improvement and optimisation. Excellent team player with the ability to drive and deliver complex projects. Ability to manage and work across multiple concurrent projects, energetic and self-driven. Confidence and demonstrable experience of presenting to senior stakeholders. Excellent written and verbal communication, organization, time-management, process and project management skills. Ability to work as part of a geographically diverse team. Values Demonstrates and embraces Westcon-Comstor values of Excellence, Innovation, Partnership, Integrity and Empowerment. Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
